  "21-61": (
    caption: [Determinants of organ size. A tissue may tune cell growth, proliferation, death, or a combination of these to regulate size. Extracellular matrix deposition also contributes, especially in animal tissues such as bone and cartilage, and in plants.],
    path: "../fig/image_place_holder.png"
